{"lemma":"سُجَّدُ","slug":"سُجَّدُ","root":"س.ج.د","root_slug":"س-ج-د","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ج-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ساجِد","root":"سجد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":23},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n18911"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8F%D8%AC%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%AF%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"active participle of سَجَدَ (sajada): prostrated","tags":["active","form-of","participle"],"examples":[{"text":"وَعَهِدْنَا إِلَى إِبْرَاهِيمَ وَإِسْمَاعِيلَ أَن طَهِّرَا بَيْتِيَ لِلطَّائِفِينَ وَالْعَاكِفِينَ وَالرُّكَّعِ السُّجُودِ"},{"text":"فَإِذَا سَوَّيْتُهُ وَنَفَخْتُ فِيهِ مِنْ رُوحِي فَقَعُوا لَهُ سَاجِدِينَ"}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n18911","headword_ar":"سَجَدَ","root":"sjd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Msb, K, &c.,) [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sujuwdN","text_ar":"سُجُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, lowly, humble,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"submissive;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaDaEa","text_ar":"خَضَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, K, TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taTaAmana","text_ar":"تَطَامَنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*al~a","text_ar":"ذَلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he bent him-self down towards the ground:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Bekr, TA: [and such is often meant by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaDaEa","text_ar":"خَضَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taTaAmana","text_ar":"تَطَامَنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) [or it has both of these significations combined; i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, lowly, humble,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"submissive, bending himself down;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for] the primary signification of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~ujuwdu","text_ar":"السُّجُودُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ta*al~ulF","text_ar":"تَذَلُّلً"},{"kind":"text","text":"together with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taTaA^omunN","text_ar":"تَطَاْمُنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taTaAmunN","text_ar":"تَطَامُنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Bd in ii. 32.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Asjd","text_ar":"اسجد","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He lowered his head, and bent himself;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, S, Mgh, K;) said of a man; (AA, S, Mgh;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and put his forehead on the ground:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) and likewise said of a camel; (S, A;) in the latter case tropical; (A;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sajada","text_ar":"سَجَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A, Mgh, Msb;) meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he lowered his head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to be ridden,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to his rider,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the occasion of his being ridden,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mounted."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b2-  The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sujuwd","text_ar":"سُجُود"},{"kind":"text","text":"of prayer is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sajada","text_ar":"سَجَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the first of the senses expl. above; (S;) and means The ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prostrating oneself;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"putting the forehead on the ground:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sajada","text_ar":"سَجَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (ISd, Msb, TA,) aor. and inf. n. as above, (ISd, TA,) signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he put his forehead on the ground:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd, Msb, TA:) but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sujuwd","text_ar":"سُجُود"},{"kind":"text","text":"to God denotes a particular manner [of doing this; i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prostrating oneself"},{"kind":"text","text":"in prayer"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by dropping gently upon the knees, placing the palms of the hands on the ground, a little before the place of the knees, and then putting the nose and forehead on the ground, the former first, between the two hands"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) ―         -b3-  It is said of Kisrà, in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna yasojudo lilT~aAliE","text_ar":"كَانَ يَسْجُدْ لِلطَّالِع"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He used to lower himself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bend himself down, to the arrow passing beyond the butt, going over it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"which they used to reckon like that which hit the butt; meaning that he used to concede to the shooter thereof: or, accord. to Az, it means that he used to lower his head when his arrow was elevated [too high] above the object shot at, in order that the arrow might be rightly directed, and might hit the circle. (TA.) ―         -b4-  And [as salutation is often accompanied with a bending of the body,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sujuwdN","text_ar":"سُجُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (assumed tropical:)  The act of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saluting."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA.) [You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sajada lahu","text_ar":"سَجَدَ لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He saluted him."},{"kind":"text","text":"And also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He paid respect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honour, to him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"magnified him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"see Ham p. 294.] ―         -b5-  You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sajadati Aln~axolapu","text_ar":"سَجَدَتِ النَّخْلَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The palm-tree bent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inclined,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, Mgh, TA,) by reason of the abundance of its fruit. (Mgh.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~afiynapu tasojudu lilr~iyHi","text_ar":"السَّفِينَةُ تَسْجُدُ لِلرِّيحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The ship bends,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inclines, by the influence of the wind."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa A@ln~ajomu wa A@l$~ajaru yasojudaAni","text_ar":"وَ ا@لنَّجْمُ وَ ا@لشَّجَرُ يَسْجُدَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [lv. 5], means, accord. to Fr, (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And the herbs and the trees"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"turn towards the sun and incline with it until the afternoon-shade becomes broken:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the herbs and the trees humbly submit to his will."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, Jel.) The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sujuwd","text_ar":"سُجُود"},{"kind":"text","text":"of inanimate things to God we understand, in the Kur, as denoting obedience to that whereto they are made subservient, and as a fact to be believed without inquiry into the manner thereof. (I'Ab, L.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He stood erect:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, Msb, K:) so in the dial. of Teiyi. (Msb.) It is said in the K, immediately after the mention of the first signification and this last, that thus the verb has two contr. meanings: but it may be said that there is no [necessary, or absolute,] contrariety between"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxuDuwE","text_ar":"الخُضُوع"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlAinotiSaAb","text_ar":"الاِنْتِصَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":". (MF.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sajidato","text_ar":"سَجِدَتْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rijoluhu","text_ar":"رِجْلُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His leg became inflated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"swollen."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","S","A","K","TA","Mgh","ISd","AHn","Lth"]}]}}